]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"a279d1",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Short-bowel syndrome",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sup",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"a"
]
},
"; undigested carbohydrates in the colon are metabolized to D-lactate by bacteria"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ea9a40",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Intermittent confusion; slurred speech; ataxia; increased anion gap metabolic acidosis with normal serum lactate level"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e2bc60",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Antibiotics (e.g., metronidazole or neomycin) directed toward bowel flora; restriction of dietary carbohydrates"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"0f39b2",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Diagnosis requires measurement of D-lactate because D-isomer is not measured by conventional assays for serum lactate"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
}
]
}
]
